NATION BRIEFS																																												Idukki (Kerala), Oct. 20 (PTI): A couple were arrested today and remanded in custody for chaining their three-year-old child to a dog. The child has been moved to a juvenile home. Benny and Manju told police that they often left the child chained with the dog when they went out for work.																																												New Delhi (PTI): Varun Gandhi escaped unhurt after a Maruti Esteem hit his car from the side on Saturday night. The incident took place near Khan Market. No complaint has been registered.																																												Aurangabad (PTI): Additional sessions judge Ajay Chavan, 45, was found dead under mysterious circumstances at his residence on Saturday in Aurangabad district of Maharashtra, police said. The police declined to comment whether it was suicide and said investigations were under way.																																												Vellore (PTI): A security guard travelling by a goods train was allegedly murdered by two colleagues who threw the body on the platform at Jolarpet in Vellore district. Police said Bhaskar, 53, working with a security service agency in Bangalore, was travelling to Delhi on Tuesday with colleagues Ravi, 26, and Navin, 27.																																												Lucknow (PTI): The Uttar Pradesh government has banned corporal punishment in schools. Officials said, the order bans pricking, slapping, solitary confinement, electric shocks, making the children run, beating them with sticks and making them sit on their knees. The children feel humiliated by the punishment, state chief secretary P.K. Mishra said. It also violated the human rights of the children, he added.																																												 Ahmedabad (PTI): Six prisoners escaped on Friday night from a sub-jail in Kadi town of north Gujarat, police have said. Four policemen have been booked for negligence in connection with this incident.

